    <p class="terminal-list__description">
      Oolong teas are partially oxidized, resulting in a wide range of  flavors and aromas. 
      Called “Black Dragon” in Chinese, Oolong teas are cultivated in mainland China and Taiwan. 
      Oolong teas can be steeped multiple times, each time giving a unique taste. We recommend testing 
      your chosen Oolongs to determine if they are good for consistent multiple steepings
    </p>

