    <p class="terminal-list__description">
      Earl Grey Tea is flavored by oil of Bergamot, a fragrant citrus fruit, 
      resulting in a delicate floral and smooth tasting flavor. Traditionally, 
      Earl Grey was made from black tea, but it is now also available in other varieties, 
      such as Green and Oolong. Adding milk often enhances the floral flavor in Earl Grey tea. 
      If you decide to include Earl Grey Tea in your menu, also consider adding a London Fog, 
      a latte made with Earl Grey, milk and vanilla syrup
    </p>

